|RKB-- Priests of Set --------------------------------------------|000

The Priests of Set, also known as the Dark Clerics, are devoted to
Set's old and absolute evil.  They do not heal the world, defend the
innocent, or pretend that their power is gentle.  They make bargains
with darkness, perform cruel rituals, and draw strength from obedience
to their god.

Set's priests are ritualists.  Their powers include evil prayer,
summoned darkness, curses, malign rites, soul-scratching torments,
leprosy, destruction, feigned death, raising the dead, stealing
alignment, and other works that are not meant for clean hands.  Their
ceremonial dagger is the center of their devotion and many of their
rites.

This guild is best suited for players who want a dark, religious,
ritual-focused path.  Expect an evil theme, hostile magic, and a
relationship with Set that is not forgiving.  The guild is not a neutral
priesthood with a different color of robe; it is a commitment to a
god of corruption, fear, death, and power.

Joining begins at the Temple of Set.  The temple does not welcome the
good-hearted, and Set's doors judge those who approach.  If you are
accepted inside, the initiation is performed with the ceremonial dagger.
New adventurers should understand the tone before taking that step:
the Priests of Set are meant to be sinister, dangerous, and devoted.

Useful starting notes:

  Guild name:       Priests of Set / Dark Clerics
  Internal guild:   Cleric_Set
  Newbie checkout:  checkout set
  Theme:            evil rituals, curses, darkness, death, devotion

Ask a current Priest of Set, or an immortal, if you need help finding
the temple or understanding whether this path fits your character.
